<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="654" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[132,777,1118,1195]" pageId="11" pageNumber="654">ETYMOLOGY. — This species is named for the elegant curves of the dorsomedian carinae on the first tergite, which remind of the shape of a violin.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
